## Important Notes

> [!CAUTION]
> **NEVER commit the actual `.env.local` file to version control!**
> 
> The `.env.example` file should only contain placeholder values.
> Actual keys must be obtained from the Supabase dashboard.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Service Role Key Security**
> 
> The `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` should NEVER be used in frontend code.
> It bypasses all Row Level Security policies and should only be used in:
> - Edge Functions (server-side)
> - Backend scripts
> - Database migrations

## Getting Your Supabase Keys

1. Go to your Supabase project dashboard
2. Navigate to Settings â†’ API
3. Copy the following:
   - **Project URL**: Use for `VITE_SUPABASE_URL`
   - **anon public**: Use for `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
   - **service_role**: Only for backend (never in frontend)

## Setup Instructions

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone <repository-url>
cd dark-hubble

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install

# 3. Copy environment template
cp .env.example .env.local

# 4. Edit .env.local and add your actual keys
nano .env.local

# 5. Run development server
npm run dev
```
